summary: It cracks me up when people say Finn leaving the FO doesn’t make sense.
body:
It cracks me up when people say Finn leaving the FO doesn’t make sense.

And I’ll admit, that was my first thought, watching TFA the first time .. how does a brainwashed slave-soldier just.. leave ?

But you know what else doesn’t make sense? That Leia could be tortured and mind probed by Vader and come out looking annoyed at most. That Han, whose motivation for just about everything is getting a paycheck, would suddenly come back to fight the Empire. That R2 and 3PO just happened to crash on the same planet their old master grew up on and happen to run into his son. That multiple Jedi including Dooku, Krell,and I believe Vos, had been raised and conditioned by the Jedi Order since they were very young all, not only left the Order but became Sith or wanted to. That everything within a small radius doesn’t burst into flames whenever someone ignites a lightsaber including the person holding it.

Some of those things are explained as “The Force wills it”. Or as “it’s a movie. If we made everything make sense, we’d have a boring story”. So yea maybe Finn deserting the First Order doesn’t make sense. But I see no reason why we can’t just say it was the Force and move on. And what would be more entertaining.. trying to come up with a perfect explanation… or having a character unlike we’ve ever seen in a Star Wars movie?

Also I’m pretty sure it’s all explained in the EU materials on Finn, which I get not everyone has time to buy and read, I certainly don’t. But that’s what Google and wiki pages are for.
